    "The linear layer shares network parameters with the input word embedding network.",
    "Sharing parameters achieves token lookup consistency and memory savings.",
    "The probability distribution for the predicted token depends conditionally on the joint probability distribution of the contextualized tokens at prior positions.",
    "Experiments revealed that the probability distribution for the set of predicted tokens follows a power law decay that is characteristic of general language statistics where the n th most frequent word occurs with a frequency of 1/n (Wolfram 2002).",
    "Therefore, only a few words will rank highest in probability."
